Package: bhc
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian Hierarchical Clustering
Version: 1.0
Date: 2021-04-06
Author: Michael C. Grundler
Maintainer: Michael C. Grundler <mcgrundler@gmail.com>
Description: Bayesian Hierarchical Clustering is a greedy agglomerative
  clustering method that approximates a Dirichlet process mixture model.
  Package bhc can be used to run the Bayesian Hierarchical Clustering
  algorithm on normally distributed and multinomially distributed data.
NeedsCompilation: yes
License: CC0
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
